	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Two men were shot dead in Bellville, Cape Town, on Wednesday afternoon, Western Cape police said. An unknown group of suspects fled Durban Road after opening fire around 13:45, and were still on the run, said Captain FC van Wyk. The men, aged 19 and 20, had not yet been identified. Police were investigating the motive for the murders. Anyone with further information can contact the investigating officer Warrant Officer Shaun Jansen on 082 811 1223 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  